  "helpSheetTitle": "How this works",
  "helpDismiss": "Got it",
  "helpHomeTitle": "Home",
  "helpHome1": "Swipe left or right anywhere on the screen — not just the tab bar — to jump between Home, Explore, Scan, and Profile.",
  "helpHome2": "Pull down on this page to force-refresh your subscription status and nearby gym data.",
  "helpHome3": "Each promo card at the top is a shortcut — tap one to jump directly to that section of the app.",
  "helpExploreTitle": "Explore",
  "helpExplore1": "Double-tap the handle bar at the bottom to jump the gym list to full screen. Single-tap steps it between the slim peek and half-open view.",
  "helpExplore2": "Double-tap a map pin to open that gym's full profile directly — a single tap just shows a quick preview card.",
  "helpExplore3": "Swipe left or right on the map to switch tabs. You don't need to reach the tab bar at the bottom.",
  "helpScanTitle": "Check In",
  "helpScan1": "Point your camera at the gym's QR code — it detects automatically. A confirmation card appears; tap 'Check in' to log your visit.",
  "helpScan2": "Step back about a metre from the code if the scanner is struggling. Getting too close actually reduces accuracy.",
  "helpScan3": "Swipe left or right on the camera view to switch to another tab without leaving camera mode.",
  "helpProfileTitle": "Profile",
  "helpProfile1": "Pull down on this page to force-refresh your visit count — handy right after a check-in when the number hasn't updated yet.",
  "helpProfile2": "Swipe left or right anywhere on this page to switch tabs — the whole screen responds, not just the bottom bar.",
  "helpProfile3": "Tap 'Manage' under your active plan to see upgrade, pause, and cancel options — all subscription actions are behind that one tap.",

  "helpGymDetail1": "The tier band at the top tells you exactly which plan level unlocks this gym. If it is greyed out, your current plan does not cover this venue.",
  "helpGymDetail2": "Tap 'Check in here' on this page — you don't need to switch to the Scan tab when you are standing at the gym entrance.",
  "helpGymDetail3": "No plan? Tap 'Buy a day pass' for a single-visit ticket charged to your saved payment method immediately.",

  "helpPlans1": "Tap a plan card to compare 1, 3, 6, and 12-month prices — the tier stays the same but the per-month rate drops for longer terms.",
  "helpPlans2": "Each tier unlocks a different set of gyms. Check a gym's detail page to see exactly which tier it requires.",
  "helpPlans3": "You can upgrade your tier at any time mid-subscription — you only pay the prorated difference for the remaining days.",

  "helpSubscription1": "Visit count resets at the start of every billing cycle. Unused visits do not carry over to next month.",
  "helpSubscription2": "Tapping 'Upgrade' here switches your tier mid-cycle and charges only the prorated difference — not the full new-tier price.",
  "helpSubscription3": "Cancelling stops future charges but your access stays active until the current paid period ends.",

  "helpBilling1": "Saved payment methods auto-charge on renewal — you don't need to re-enter them each month.",
  "helpBilling2": "Tap any billing row to expand it and see the full receipt, including which plan was active that period.",
  "helpBilling3": "If a payment fails, a red banner appears at the top of this page. Tap it immediately to retry before your access is paused.",

  "helpCheckinSuccess1": "Your check-in is already logged — you don't need to show this screen to the gym staff. They can see your entry on their own display.",
  "helpCheckinSuccess2": "This check-in used one of your monthly visits. Pull down on the Profile tab to see your updated count.",
  "helpCheckinSuccess3": "Something wrong with this check-in? Tap the support link below to flag it now — location context helps us fix it faster.",

  "helpNotifications1": "Gym announcements and subscription reminders appear here and stay until you clear them individually.",
  "helpNotifications2": "The red dot on the bell tab clears only after you open this list — just receiving the notification does not clear it.",
  "helpNotifications3": "To turn off a specific type of alert, go to Profile → Settings → Notifications. You can mute them without deleting them.",

  "helpSettings1": "The language toggle shows the target language, not the current one — 'AR' means tap to switch to Arabic, not that Arabic is currently active.",
  "helpSettings2": "Changing your linked phone number requires an OTP to the new number to confirm you own it.",
  "helpSettings3": "Deleting your account is instant and permanent — it cancels your active plan and removes all visit history with no recovery option.",

  "helpFilter1": "You can select multiple categories and multiple tiers at the same time — the gym list updates live as you tap each chip.",
  "helpFilter2": "Drag the handle bar at the top upward to expand the filter sheet to full height and see all options at once.",
  "helpFilter3": "Tap 'Reset' at the top-right corner to clear every active filter at once and return to the full gym list.",

  "helpSignIn1": "Type your phone number — the app checks automatically as you finish typing. If you have an account with a password, the password field slides in on its own. If you're new, tap Continue to receive your OTP.",
  "helpSignIn2": "The +962 country code is pre-filled. Type your digits starting with 7 — you can include the leading zero or leave it out, the app normalises it automatically. Both '780195112' and '0780195112' work fine.",
  "helpSignIn3": "Prefer Google? Tap 'Continue with Google' to sign in via your Google account. Google handles its own login screen — there is no OTP from GymPass. Once Google confirms you, you're signed in instantly.",
  "helpSignIn4": "Already have a GymPass password? Just finish typing your number — the password field appears automatically the moment the app recognises your account. You don't need to tap Continue first.",
  "helpSignIn5": "If you get a 'number not valid' error, make sure you haven't accidentally included the area code twice. The format is exactly 9 digits after the +962 prefix.",

  "helpOtp1": "Check your SMS inbox — the 4-digit code arrives within seconds of tapping Continue. If it doesn't appear, check that your phone signal is active.",
  "helpOtp2": "On most phones the code appears as a suggestion above the keyboard when the SMS arrives. Tap it to fill in all four digits instantly — no manual typing needed.",
  "helpOtp3": "The code is valid for 5 minutes. If it expires before you enter it, tap 'Resend code' — a new code cancels the old one, so only the latest one works.",
  "helpOtp4": "Make sure you are entering the most recent code if you tapped Resend more than once. Each resend replaces the previous code.",
  "helpOtp5": "In development mode the code is always 1234 — you don't need to check your SMS while testing the app.",

  "helpRegister1": "Only your first and last name are required to create your pass. Everything else — email, birthdate, gender — is optional and can be filled in later from Profile → Settings.",
  "helpRegister2": "Your GymPass subscription does not start here. This screen just saves your profile. You will choose a plan and pay on the next screen — nothing is charged until you confirm checkout.",
  "helpRegister3": "Your password must be at least 8 characters and include both a letter and a number. It is used for sign-in if you ever switch away from OTP or Google.",
  "helpRegister4": "If you signed in with Google, your name may already be pre-filled. You can edit it here before tapping 'Create my pass' — the name on your account will match what you set here.",
  "helpRegister5": "Read the Terms and Privacy Policy links before ticking the agreement box. They explain how your data is used, what the gyms can see about you, and how to request deletion.",

  "helpForgotPw1": "Enter the phone number you used when you signed up. We look up your account by number — not by email — so make sure it is the right one.",
  "helpForgotPw2": "Choose how to receive the reset code: by SMS to your phone, or by email if you added one to your profile. If no email is on file, SMS is the only option.",
  "helpForgotPw3": "The 4-digit reset code works exactly like the sign-in OTP — check your SMS inbox and enter it within 5 minutes before it expires.",
  "helpForgotPw4": "Your new password must be at least 8 characters long and include both a letter and a number. Avoid reusing your old password.",
  "helpForgotPw5": "After resetting, you will be taken back to the sign-in screen. Enter your phone number and tap Continue — then choose 'Sign in with password' and use your new password.",

  "helpHelpHub1": "Tap 'Contact Support' to reach our team by phone, email, or WhatsApp.",
  "helpHelpHub2": "The FAQ answers the most common questions without needing to contact anyone.",
  "helpHelpHub3": "Use 'Report Issue' to flag a bad check-in or app bug — you can attach a screenshot as evidence.",

  "helpSupportContact1": "Tapping phone, email, or WhatsApp opens the matching app directly — if the app isn't installed, the number is copied to your clipboard instead.",
  "helpSupportContact2": "Fill in the Subject and Message fields below to send a written ticket. You'll receive a reference number by reply to track it.",
  "helpSupportContact3": "WhatsApp is usually the fastest channel — our support team responds there first.",

  "helpSupportFaq1": "Tap any question to expand the answer. Tap it again to collapse.",
  "helpSupportFaq2": "The search bar looks through both questions and answers at once — useful when you know a keyword but not the category.",
  "helpSupportFaq3": "Tap a category pill (Billing, Check-in, etc.) to filter questions to that topic. You can combine a category filter with a search keyword.",

  "helpSupportReport1": "Pick the category closest to your issue — it routes your report to the right team automatically.",
  "helpSupportReport2": "Tap 'Attach evidence' to add a screenshot from your camera roll or take a new photo on the spot.",
  "helpSupportReport3": "Add the gym name if your issue is location-specific — it speeds up the investigation.",

  "helpGyms1": "Use the search bar at the top to find a gym by name or neighbourhood — results filter instantly as you type.",
  "helpGyms2": "Tap the category pills (Gym, CrossFit, Martial, Yoga) to narrow the list to the type of training you want.",
  "helpGyms3": "Tap the heart icon at the top-right to show only your saved favourites. Tap it again to return to the full list.",
  "helpGyms4": "Tap the filter icon next to the heart to filter by tier — handy if you want to see only gyms your current plan covers.",
  "helpGyms5": "The mini-map above the list shows all gyms as dots. Tap any dot to jump straight to that gym's detail page.",

  "helpWelcome1": "Your subscription is now active and your visits are loaded. Head to Explore to find a gym near you and scan in.",
  "helpWelcome2": "Visit count resets every 30 days from your subscription start date — not on the 1st of the calendar month.",
  "helpWelcome3": "Your QR code is in the Scan tab. Just open it at the gym door — no staff action needed, the scan is automatic.",
  "helpWelcome4": "You can check your remaining visits and renewal date at any time from Profile → My Subscription.",
  "helpWelcome5": "Want to train at a gym outside your tier? Tap 'Day pass' on any locked gym's detail page for a single-visit ticket.",

  "helpAddMethod1": "Card details (number, expiry, CVV) are processed by our payment provider — we never store your full card number on our servers.",
  "helpAddMethod2": "CliQ lets you link your Jordanian bank account using an alias or phone number. Charges go through your bank directly.",
  "helpAddMethod3": "Apple Pay and Google Pay are available on supported devices. We receive only a payment token — not your actual card details.",
  "helpAddMethod4": "Only one default payment method is used for subscription renewals. You can change the default anytime from the Billing page.",
  "helpAddMethod5": "You can add multiple methods and pick which one to use at checkout for day passes or upgrades.",

  "helpDayPass1": "A day pass gives you one entry to this specific gym valid for the next 24 hours. It does not count toward your monthly visit budget.",
  "helpDayPass2": "Payment is charged immediately using your default payment method. Make sure you have one saved before tapping 'Pay'.",
  "helpDayPass3": "After purchase, go to the Scan tab and scan the QR at the gym entrance. Your day pass is consumed on the first successful scan.",
  "helpDayPass4": "Day passes do not roll over — if you don't scan within 24 hours, the pass expires and the charge is not refunded.",
  "helpDayPass5": "You can only have one active day pass per gym at a time. Buy another only after the current one is used or expired."
}
